If audits result in any significant non-compliance in any element or process, a CorrectiveAction Plan to address the findings is to be prepared and implemented and a re-audit is to be carried out within 3 months.The Audits shall as a minimum cover the following elements:· Selection, Recruitment and Promotion process· Document control· Competency Assessment (As applicable)· Process for checking authenticity and Validity of certificates and endorsements· Pre-employment medical checks and control of Facilities used for medical checks· Pre-employment confirmation process for knowledge, experience, background and validity of certificates· Follow-up of disciplinary cases, and· Appraisals and Training· Compliance with local requirements4.12JOB DESCRIPTIONS OF OFFICERS AND RATINGSThe responsibilities of all officers and ratings engaged onboard are as detailed in the Vessel Operation Manual. It is the endeavor ofthe management that all ship staff shall abide by these guidelines.4.13ADMINISTRATION OF SHIP'S PERSONNELThe performance, general administration and welfare of ship's personnel shall be mainly monitored and looked after by the CrewDepartment who shall be assisted by the Master, the Technical Department and the Senior Management.They shall be established by the following procedures:· maintaining personnel records of all officers and crew members.· appraisal reports· while re-employing any staff these records shall be reviewed and due consideration shall be given to his promotional prospects ifsuitably qualified for the rank.· by encouraging and motivating seafarers and attending to all reasonable requests.· by reviewing the pay structures and the terms and conditions of the service contract annually and making necessary revisions.· arrange for timely reliefs.4.14MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS FOR OFFICERS AND CREW RECRUITMENT4.14.1MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS FOR AN OFFICERAny officer joining a vessel shall:be proficient in EnglishHold a valid certificate of competency issued by the relevant approved authority for at least the rank of appointment valid for the duration of his contract.Have undergone the medical examination as per Flag of the vessel and be found “Fit for Sea Service”.Comply with the requirements of the applicable 'Training and Qualifications Matrix' in Annex 7 and Phoenix.4.14.2MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS FOR A RATINGAny rating joining a vessel shall:be proficient in Englishhave relevant watch keeping certificate if applicable.(For watch keepers)
